Question 2  Explanation: Given, $\quad$ input is $r(t)=\alpha t u(t)$ $
R(s)=\frac{\alpha}{s^{2}}
$ From the figure, $
G(s) H(s)=\frac{K}{s(s+2)}
$ Now steady state error for Ramp input is $e_{s s} =\frac{\alpha}{K_{v}}, \text { where } \alpha \text { is the magnitude of Ramp input } $ $
\begin{aligned}  K_{v} & =\lim _{s \rightarrow 0}[s G(s) H(s)] \\
K_{v} & =\lim _{s \rightarrow 0}\begin{bmatrix}\frac{s \times K}{s(s+2)}\end{bmatrix}=\frac{K}{2}\\
\therefore \quad e_{s s} & =\frac{\alpha \times 2}{K} \\
e_{s s} & =\frac{2 \alpha}{K}
\end{aligned}
$
